                  <decoDesc>
                     
                     <summary>The manuscript contains one prefatory miniature of the annunciation and two headpieces painted in the 
                     <term key="SecondSolomonicStyle" ana="#SecondSolomonicStyle"/>. 
                     </summary>
                     
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#2v" facs="f10"/>
                        <desc>A miniature representing the <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1002Annunciation">Annunciation</ref>, in which <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4377Gabriel">Gabriel</persName>  holds a <term key="scroll" ana="#scroll"/>
                           and  performs a <term key="gestureblessing" ana="#gestureblessing">gesture of speech</term>, while <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> is spinning. The name of the owner of the manuscript,
                           <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11018TanseaK">Tanśǝʾa Krǝstos</persName>, is written above the miniature in a simple frame. Further names,including <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11019Tewogolos">Tewogolos</persName>, 
                           are written below the miniature.
                           </desc>
                        <q xml:lang="gez">ኀበ፡ ዜነዋ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ለማርያም፡ በእንተ፡ ልደቱ፡ ለክርስቶስ።</q>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
              
